title: Team Website
description: Integrity, hard work, organization, dedication and a sprinkle of creativity…these are just a few of the qualities that make us great at what we do! There is no mountain too tall for our team to tackle. We have the knowledge and know-how to prepare your home to sell and optimize its highest return. On the buy side we will work tirelessly to place you into your dream home and negotiate to ensure it comes at the best price.  We are customer driven and desire to make sure our clients have the best possible experience. Not only do we take the stress out of buying or selling by guiding you through the process, we make it an enjoyable journey.  We grew up in small towns in Nebraska and possess that hard working attitude. We know what it takes to get the job done and we aren’t afraid to roll up our sleeves to make it happen. Whether it’s buying or selling, we go the extra mile. Consulting you on everything from de-cluttering, to what paint color might best showcase your living spaces, or what to do with that pesky problem area in your basement you’ve never figured out.  We have an eye for detail and know what changes to suggest to net you the highest possible return on your home. Not only are we creative, we are business women. Daria is a graduate of Wesleyan University and the owner of several Scooters Coffee locations. She has built a very successful business from the ground up. She also has excellent marketing skills and has a background in human resources, having worked for a Fortune 500 company. Marsha has experience general contracting houses as well as whole home renovations and owns multiple rental properties throughout Lincoln. These skills, married together give us the background to give you the best possible service. Hiring us as your real estate professionals gives you peace of mind. Two sets of eyes watching over one of the biggest transactions you will make in your lifetime, two sets of eyes watching over your family, two sets of eyes making sure no detail is missed. That is the power of choosing Daria and Marsha as your REALTORS®.

title: REALTOR®
description: You loathe the typical real estate agent bio and I do too. They’re like cardboard — stiff, bland, and identical to every other bio out there. Instead of boasting about myself, let me answer some questions you might have: Will you return my calls and emails? Yes. Without question and asap I realize this is one of the major frustrations the general public has with dealing with agents.  I’ve met many Realtors who are jerks. Are you? Well, that depends on who you ask. Here's what I can tell you: I'm honest and candid. I take pride in being approachable, caring and friendly. And if you need a quick real estate brain, or a strong dose of honesty, you’re in the right place. Loyalty to family, clients, and friends is one of my core values. Want to really find out if I’m a jerk? Mess with one of those people. Do you have experience doing exactly what I need? Until you tell me what you need, there is no way of knowing. These are "strong suits" of mine: Working with new home buyers, Relocations-New Construction and Home renovators. If your need isn't represented on that list, don't worry. Contact me anyway. If I can't help, I can get you referred to an another agent who can. What kind of work are you really good at? On a personal level, I'm pretty good at cooking(I make a mean pot of chili and cinnamon rolls), and I'm not super rad at roller skating, but I love it. On a professional level, here are the skill-sets that I’ve developed over the years: Listening. Unfortunately, it’s a lost art these days. Customer service, I'll go above and beyond for you. Training, I am always taking a class and learning to better serve you, I'm your trusted real estate provider.

title: REALTOR® | Associate Broker | CRS, GRI
description: Real Estate - it's what I do, and it's all about matching people with spaces that reflect who they are.  I have contact information at my fingertips for Lincoln's best vendors, from stagers to lenders to movers to electricians - to help make your move a smooth one.  I am proud to be part of the networking and professional standard at Home Real Estate, voted "Best of Lincoln" every year for over a decade. Count on the HIGH standard.

title: Sales Associate
description: Having the right real estate agent means having an agent who is committed to helping you buy or sell your home with the highest level of expertise in your local market. This means also to help you in understanding each step of the buying or selling process. This commitment level has helped me build a remarkable track record of delivering results. Nothing is more exciting to me than the gratifying feeling I get from helping people meet their real estate needs. You can count on me to always do what's in your best interest. I pride myself on being honest, trustworthy, and knowledgeable in the real estate market. I know how important it is to find your dream home or get the best offer for your property. Therefore I will make it my responsibility to help you achieve those goals. Whether you are an experienced investor or a first time buyer, I can help you in finding the property of your dreams. Please feel free to browse my website or let me guide you every step of the way by calling or e-mailing me to set up an appointment today.

title: REALTOR®
description: I’m a native Nebraskan who has lived in Lincoln for 25 years.  Having raised two children in Southeast Lincoln and having worked in North Lincoln for 20 years, I am familiar with most of Lincoln.  Having worked in Human Resources, my forté is helping people find what they need and where to get it.  I believe ‘home is where the heart is,’ and I love the challenge of helping people find their “Heart.”

title: ABR, GRI, PSA, SRS
description: Rhonda Rogers, ABR, GRI, PSA, SRS, is a REALTOR® with HOME Real Estate servicing the Lincoln, Nebraska area. She became an active member in the REALTOR® Association of Lincoln in 2016. She currently serves and is an active member of several RAL committees and has been elected to serve on the Ed Trust Board for several terms. In addition to her local involvement, she participates at the state level and currently sits on several committees and has completed the Nebraska REALTORS® Association Leadership Academy. As a Lincoln native, she attended UNL and graduated in 2007 with a degree in Early Inclusive Childhood Education. She is also active on the office Social Committee for HOME Real Estate. Rhonda has furthered her real estate career by obtaining several designations. She has also attended a Ninja installation and completed the LeadingRE training. In her spare time, Rhonda enjoys spending time with family, especially her two sons, and friends, and the occasional gardening or crafting project when possible. She also volunteers with several local community committee boards, including previous service on her neighborhood association board, private neighborhood pool, and local elementary PTA.

title: Randy and Roma Amundson
description: Roma has been a Realtor since 1996.  She has the following professional designations:  Certified Residential Specialist, Graduate Realtor Institute, e-Pro, Accredited Buyer Representative, At Home with Diversity.Randy began his career in real estate in 2012 after completing 20 years of active duty with the Nebraska Army National Guard.  His experience in home construction, architectural drawing, and drafting make him note critical issues in the homes that we tour. Both are dedicated to meeting the needs and objectives of their clients – to facilitate the sale and purchase of homes in accordance with the housing requirements of their clients and their financial capabilities.  We strive to make the selling and buying processes fun, enjoyable, informative, and trouble-free.  We are interested in serving YOU!

title: Sales Associate
description: I am originally from Seward, NE, and have lived in Lincoln for over 30 years, giving me extensive knowledge of the Nebraska real estate market. I love helping people, and as a real estate agent, I have had the opportunity to help people from all walks of life. In my free time, I love to golf and spend time with my family. Lincoln is a fantastic community that genuinely is a big-small town. My 20+ years of experience have given me the ability to help clients throughout the buying and selling process no matter what problems may come up.

title: Sales Associate
description: Hello! I am committed to providing personal service for each client. I am passionate about helping you achieve your goals and will stay focused on you. I will listen to your needs and help you find that special home in a timely manner.  If it matters to you ...it matters to Connie! Contact me today - I'd love an opportunity to earn your business!  AFFILIATIONS & EDUCATION Member of National Association of REALTORS® (NAR) Member of Nebraska REALTORS® Association (NRA) Member of REALTORS® Assocation of Lincoln (RAL) Graduate of REALTOR® Institute (GRI) Master's Degree in Business Education Bachelor's of Science in Business Education

title: Sales Associate
description: Hello! I'm a habitual remodeler, and love finding the potential in those homes that just need a little love. Or a lot of love. I've spent several years in the world of remodeling, new construction and design, which helps me help you imagine how you could make that house in your favorite neighborhood work for your family. When I'm not working on my own fixer-upper, you can probably find me in some sort of musical endeavor, either playing violin in Lincoln's Symphony Orchestra, singing with a jazz band, huddled in my office composing, or giving lessons to the next generation of musicians. I spent 16 years as a college professor, helping students grow as musicians and find their musical voice. My three boys don't appreciate my assistance with their musical endeavors, however, but we have fun taking care of our acreage, where we inherited Koi fish, an orchard, a bass pond, and a huge garden where my husband occasionally lets me help. Let me know how I can help you!

title: Sales Associate
description: I served as faculty, administrator and project manager at the University for 25 years ~ prior to the start of my Real Estate career in 2006. Designations: To earn a designation, a REALTOR® has taken coursework and demonstrated specific skills, performance and knowledge in a particular area of the real estate industry. In addition to my Master of Science Education degree (MSEd), I am a Certified Residential Specialist (CRS), Accredited Buyers Representative (ABR), Graduate of Realtor Institute (GRI), Senior's Real Estate Specialists (SRES 55+) and a Notary. Life-long Learning is very important! Code of Ethics: The Code establishes time-honored and baseline principles that come from the collective experiences of REALTORS® since the Code of Ethics was first established in 1913. Those principles can be loosely defined as:               *Loyalty to clients  *Fiduciary (legal) duty to clients  *Cooperation with competitors  *Truthfulness in statements and advertising  * Non-interference in exclusive relationships that other REALTORS® have with their clients. What it Means to be a REALTOR®: A REALTOR® is a member of the local, state and National Association of Realtors and subscribes to its strict Code of Ethics. Continuing education is required to maintain a license and is critical in staying informed and up to date with technology and the relevant industries.

title: REALTOR
description: Thrilled to dive into the business of real estate in the City of Lincoln! Whether it’s your business or home, please don’t hesitate to reach out to me about marketing, buying/selling, referrals, valuations, or even if you just want to chat about the real estate market in general.
